#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:4
msgid ""
"This page describes changes you need to be aware of when upgrading from "
"Istio 1.2.x to 1.3.x. Here, we detail cases where we intentionally broke "
"backwards compatibility. We also mention cases where backwards "
"compatibility was preserved but new behavior was introduced that would be"
" surprising to someone familiar with the use and operation of Istio 1.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:12
msgid "Installation and upgrade"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:14
msgid ""
"We simplified the configuration model for Mixer and removed support for "
"adapter-specific and template-specific Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs)"
" entirely in 1.3. Please move to the new configuration model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:18
msgid ""
"We removed the Mixer CRDs from the system to simplify the configuration "
"model, improve Mixer’s performance in Kubernetes deployments, and improve"
" reliability in various Kubernetes environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:23
msgid "Traffic management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:25
msgid ""
"Istio now captures all ports by default. If you don’t specify container "
"ports to intentionally bypass Envoy, you must opt out of port capturing "
"with the ``traffic.sidecar.istio.io/excludeInboundPorts`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:29
msgid ""
"Protocol sniffing is now enabled by default. Disable protocol sniffing "
"with the ``--set pilot.enableProtocolSniffing=false`` option when you "
"upgrade to get the previous behavior. To learn more see our `protocol "
"selection page </docs/ops/configuration/traffic-management/protocol-"
"selection/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:35
msgid ""
"To specify a hostname in multiple namespaces, you must select a single "
"host using a `Sidecar resource "
"</docs/reference/config/networking/sidecar/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:39
msgid "Trust domain validation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:41
msgid ""
"Trust domain validation is new in Istio 1.3. If you only have one trust "
"domain or you don’t enable mutual TLS through authentication policies, "
"there is nothing you must do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:45
msgid ""
"To opt-out the trust domain validation, include the following flag in "
"your Helm template before upgrading to Istio 1.3: ``--set "
"pilot.env.PILOT_SKIP_VALIDATE_TRUST_DOMAIN=true``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:50
msgid "Secret discovery service"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:52
msgid ""
"In Istio 1.3, we are taking advantage of improvements in Kubernetes to "
"issue certificates for workload instances more securely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:55
msgid ""
"Kubernetes 1.12 introduces ``trustworthy`` JWTs to solve these issues. "
"`Kubernetes 1.13 "
"<https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/CHANGELOG/CHANGELOG-1.13.md>`_"
" introduced the ability to change the value of the ``aud`` field to a "
"value other than the API server. The ``aud`` field represents the "
"audience in Kubernetes. To better secure the mesh, Istio 1.3 only "
"supports ``trustworthy`` JWTs and requires the audience, the value of the"
" ``aud`` field, to be ``istio-ca`` when you enable SDS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/1.3.x/announcing-1.3/upgrade-notes/index.rst:64
msgid ""
"Before upgrading to Istio 1.3 with SDS enabled, see our blog post on "
"`trustworthy JWTs and SDS </blog/2019/trustworthy-jwt-sds/>`_."
msgstr ""

